Take their grain bowl as an example, you're going to spend $13 for a "bowl" portion and get enough faro to feed a rabbit and a couple of colorful tomatoes to make it pretty.  Stonefruit is one of the healthier options in the neighborhood, but it should only be entertained for a light snack and a load off your wallet.

Only plastic ones, I’ve tried to cut the bread with it, but it didn’t work. When I asked the girls behind the counter, they told me the dishwasher was on and that it will take a minute or so. But after 10 minutes, when my eggs where cold, I had to ask again. She was looking at me like, what are you asking? There was nothing she could do. Then I’ve heard her talking about me. This café is great for sweet specialty drinks—like their fall edition latte with Maple and Cayenne—and tasty vegan or GF baked goods. I’ve had a few lunch dishes that were pricey but healthy and filing with lots of veggies and fruits. I like to meet friends here since it’s convenient to Fort Greene, Bed-Stuy, and Clinton Hill neighbors. We can usually find a table in the front within about 10 minutes of ordering. If I’m by myself, I try to sit in the quiet back room with the plants. But both tend to be crowded during business hours on the weekdays with freelancers and coffee shop squatters. I’ve tried the WiFi but it seems to go in and out, so I probably would not bring my laptop to study and would stick to reading books here instead.  My only other critique is that the avocado toast has a bit too thick of a slice of bread compared to the amount of avo smash on top. Would not order it here.

Soooo hipster! It is amazing the transformation that could take place from being outside the cafe to walking in.  We all know the grim and grubby Bed-Stuy, and we also know how slowly the area is gentrifying and cafes/restaurants are popping up everywhere. While people are smoking crack only a few feet away, the moment you walk in to Stonefruit, you forget the grittiness of the outdoors.  The decor suits the earthy farm to table vibe going on with plants everywhere and tables and chairs made from restored wood. In the backroom if I'm not mistaken they sell plants etc. Yes, the vibe is immensely chill. I came here for breakfast and ordered the Avocado Smash on Shewolf, White Fish on Shewolf and the Yogurt Pot. Also ordered a cappuccino and mocha. The employee taking my order was friendly and very understanding (because I was indecisive).  Each dish had a world of flavor and you can taste the care going into make it. They use super fresh, healthy and organic ingredients. I am a total fan of the white fish toast, an absolute must get if you come here.  The coffees were very very strong, some might say that's a good thing, but I feel like it could be a little less and it  would be a beautiful 5 star coffee.  You may be someone just coming for breakfast with friends or you may be someone looking for a chill place to work with your laptop or read book. Either way Stonefruit knows how to please em all.  I'll definitely be back here sometime soon.
